2. T-Rex Sip-N-Puff "Rubber Chicken" Edition — game design reference
========================================================================

The AAC Trainer (stim_games/aac_trainer.py) implements the "Chicken
Challenge" gameplay described in Michael Kadie's T-Rex Sip-N-Puff
Rubber Chicken Edition documentation, §3 "Maker Faire Engagement: The
Chicken Challenge Game". Design credit: Michael Kadie.

========================================================================
3. AAC symbol sets (referenced, not redistributed)
========================================================================

The bundled example menus (`menus/*.menu`, `menus/*_with_games.menu`)
reference image filenames conventionally supplied by the T-Rex Talker
installer. Those images are not redistributed with this repository;
they retain whatever license the installer ships them under. The
upstream Credits.md lists at minimum:

  - ARASAAC (Aragonese Portal of AAC) .... CC BY-NC-SA
  - Mulberry Symbols ..................... CC BY-SA
  - Sclera ............................... CC BY-NC

If you redistribute any of those symbols bundled with this overlay,
preserve the original license notices.

========================================================================
4. Sound generation (optional developer tool only)
========================================================================

`tools/make_trainer_sounds.py` is an optional, developer-side script
that can call any of several third-party text-to-speech engines
(gTTS, pyttsx3, Piper). None of those engines are bundled here.
Their respective licenses apply to anyone who installs them separately.

========================================================================
5. CircuitPython / Adafruit libraries (runtime dependency)
========================================================================

This repository relies on the CircuitPython runtime and several
Adafruit libraries to execute on the device. Those are not
redistributed here and retain their own upstream licenses (MIT for
most of them, Apache 2.0 for some). The Credits.md in T-Rex Talker
provides attribution.
